# Design System

## Background
The global background is `#F6F6F3` (warm off-white) with a fixed dot-grid overlay. Both layers are defined in `layout.tsx` as `fixed inset-0` divs with negative z-index — do NOT add opaque backgrounds to sections or they will cover the dots.

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT — section with transparent/glass background so dots show through
<section className="section-padding">
  <div className="bg-white/60 backdrop-blur-sm border border-black/10 rounded-2xl p-6" />
</section>

// ❌ WRONG — kills the dot pattern
<section className="bg-white">...</section>
```

## Color Palette
- Background base: `#F6F6F3`
- Dot color: `#c8c8c4`
- Card / surface: `bg-white/60 backdrop-blur-sm`
- Borders: `border-black/10`
- Hover overlay: `hover:bg-black/5`
- Primary background: `bg-black` (use `.gradient-bg` utility)
- Gradient text: `.gradient-text` utility (`from-black to-gray-600`)

## Button Colors
All non-gradient, non-destructive buttons use a **black background with white text**. Hover darkens slightly.

Tailwind tokens defined in `tailwind.config.ts`:
- `btn-base` → `#000000`
- `btn-hover` → `#1a1a1a`

```tsx
// ✅ Correct button backgrounds (use named Tailwind tokens)
variant="default"   → bg-btn-base text-white hover:bg-btn-hover
variant="outline"   → bg-btn-base text-white hover:bg-btn-hover  (border kept)
variant="secondary" → bg-btn-base text-white hover:bg-btn-hover
variant="ghost"     → hover:bg-btn-base hover:text-white
variant="gradient"  → gradient-bg text-white  (keep blue→violet, no change)

// ❌ Do NOT use bg-background, bg-primary, bg-secondary, or any light fill for buttons
// ❌ Do NOT use text-foreground on buttons — always text-white
```

## Spacing & Layout
- Section padding: `section-padding` utility → `py-20 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`
- Max width wrapper: `container-max` utility → `max-w-7xl mx-auto`

## Navbar Glass Effect (on scroll)
```tsx
className="bg-[#F6F6F3]/80 backdrop-blur-md border-b border-black/10 shadow-sm"
```

## Footer
Always use `bg-[#0f0f0f] text-gray-400` — the footer is intentionally dark.
